						               													<description>Welcome to Azetta, where traveling merchants put on trade shows with enchanted tapestries to win the sales from shoppers. Stitchcraft is a two-player strategy card game that plays in 15 to 20 minutes where players have the same deck of 40 cards, 5 copies each of 8 colored tapestries, and are racing to have 7 of the 8 colors face up on the table or 4 copies of one color face up on the table.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Stitchcraft won the Implementation of Simplicity award at CinCityCon&amp;rsquo;s 2019 design contest for being easy to learn while retaining strategic depth.  Turns are composed of each player drawing a card and then taking two actions. An action can be either placing a tapestry from hand face down on the table OR taking a face down tapestry and flipping it face up, activating the power of that color. Each color has a unique effect based on the Pattern set chosen at the start of each game. If players ever get tired of one Pattern set they can simply change to a new Pattern for an entirely different play experience. Will you enter the market and prove to be the wiliest weaver?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
